PRIME Minister Kassim Majaliwa, Wednesday, tabled budget estimates for the 2022/23 FY in Dodoma, asking the August House to approve 148.9bn/-, an amount which will capacitate his office in undertaking the planned activities for the next financial year. Outlining several priorities geared to speed up the implementation of national strategic projects including infrastructures and ICT, the Premier said out of the requested amount, 101.4bn/- is  for recurrent budget. Disaggregating further, Mr Majaliwa said a total of 4.7bn/- will be used for implementation of various development activities. Reading the 85 page budget speech, the Premier also requested the Parliamentarians to endorse a total of 132.7bn/- for Parliament Fund. Out of the requested amount, the PM said 127.3bn/- is for recurrent expenditure and the remaining 5.4bn/- will be used for development. “Allow me to submit,” said Prime Minister after reading the budget speech.